                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="datasvc-note" value="&lt;b&gt;External Data Services consumed&lt;br/&gt;during Enrichment (Steps 5–7):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size:11px;&quot;&gt;• MCA Control Data — via &lt;b&gt;SFTP&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;• Policy Data Service — &lt;b&gt;REST API&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;• Common Ref Data Services —&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Risk Taxonomy · Entitlement · Email&lt;/font&gt;" style="shape=callout;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#D6B656;fontSize=12;align=left;spacingLeft=8;perimeter=calloutPerimeter;size=15;position=0.5;direction=south;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1480" y="1060" width="260" height="130" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="actor-note" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;Actors &amp;amp; Roles&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align:left;line-height:190%;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Any Citi Employee (Initiator):&lt;/b&gt; Identifies the conflict of interest. Logs into GCOI Angular UI, creates and saves the COI record (Steps 1–3). Receives email notification on return and informs R&amp;amp;C of required changes.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Risk &amp;amp; Control Team (Enricher):&lt;/b&gt; Receives email notification on new COI. Opens record from review queue, enriches it by linking MCAs (SFTP), internal policies (REST API) and reference data (Steps 4–7), then submits the complete package to CIBA (Step 8). On return, updates and resubmits.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;CIBA Team (Checker):&lt;/b&gt; Opens enriched COI, verifies parties and details against internal/external databases, cross-references existing relationships, applies Credible Challenge to ensure completeness and accuracy (Steps 9–12), then makes the final Accept or Return decision.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;GCOI System (COI Service):&lt;/b&gt; Single backend service managing all business logic. Persists records to COI DB, fires email triggers (on Create → R&amp;amp;C; on Return → Business Team), manages all status transitions, and provides an Export Service for audit reports.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Lifecycle &amp;amp; Monitoring:&lt;/b&gt; Active COIs are placed on the Watch List for ongoing monitoring. When conflict is fully resolved, a user (R&amp;amp;C or CIBA) initiates retirement — COI is formally eliminated from the active inventory.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;fillColor=#EBF5FB;strokeColor=#2E86C1;align=left;spacingLeft=14;spacingRight=14;spacingTop=10;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="15" y="1048" width="1450" height="340" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="status-note" value="&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size:17px;&quot;&gt;COI Status Lifecycle&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align:left;font-size:13px;line-height:210%;&quot;&gt;⬤ &lt;b&gt;DRAFT&lt;/b&gt; — Created and saved by employee. Not yet reviewed.&lt;br/&gt;⬤ &lt;b&gt;UNDER REVIEW&lt;/b&gt; — Enriched by R&amp;amp;C and submitted to CIBA.&lt;br/&gt;⬤ &lt;b&gt;RETURNED&lt;/b&gt; — CIBA requires corrections. Sent back to business team for rework.&lt;br/&gt;⬤ &lt;b&gt;ACTIVE &amp;amp; ONGOING&lt;/b&gt; — Formally accepted by CIBA. Placed on Watch List. Monitored.&lt;br/&gt;⬤ &lt;b&gt;RETIRED / ELIMINATED&lt;/b&gt; — Conflict resolved. Removed from active inventory.&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;fillColor=#FEF9E7;strokeColor=#F39C12;align=left;spacingLeft=14;spacingRight=14;spacingTop=10;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1770" y="1048" width="550" height="265" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
